<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="plan-v">plan <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /plæn/    美 /plæn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>计划；筹划：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>planned economy and market economy 
计划经济与市场经济</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>To complete the project <strong>as planned</strong>, we’ll have to work two more hours a day.
为了按计划完成这个项目，我们将不得不每天加班两个小时。</p><footer>2008 湖南</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Planning is good, but doing is better.
要计划，更要有行动。</p><footer>2016 浙江书面表达</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>打算：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>plan on (doing) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is planning on introducing me to her parents.
她正打算把我介绍给她的父母。</p><footer>2008 广东</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>plan to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Judy and I plan to play table tennis tomorrow. 
我和朱迪打算明天打乒乓球。</p><footer>2008 天津</footer></div>

<h4 id="3-design">3.★ <strong>设计 (design)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>plan an essay / a garden 
构思文章/设计花园</p></div></div>